
                                            Cato Manor residents at an informal settlement were left homeless when a blaze razed their homes to the ground on Saturday.
                                         JOHANNESBURG – Several people have been displaced after their informal homes were burned to the ground on Cato Manor in Durban on Saturday. Emergency services say one person sustained minor injuries and was treated at the scene. Rescue Care's Garrith Jamieson says the cause of the fire is not known. “The Durban Fire department worked quickly to extinguish the blaze. One person sustained minor injuries and was stabilised on scene by paramedics before transported to a nearby hospital for the further care that he needed.”Jamieson says the cause of the fire remains unclear. “The South African Police Service were in attendance and will be investigating further.”